@node GETEPS
@remark Object Queries

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETEPS                                                                      @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets coordinates and information for an EPS object.

@{B}geteps@{UB} [POSITION stem] [FRAME string]
[CONTENTOFFSET stem] [CONTENTSCALE stem]
[ROTATION stem] [ABOUT stem] [CONSTRAIN string]
[PRINT string] [FILEINFO stem] [DOCUMENT name |
WINDOW name | OBJECTID number]

POSITION/a      Gets the coordinates.
FRAME/s         Gets the frame state.
CONTENTOFFSET/a Gets the frame contents offset.
CONTENTSCALE/a  Gets the frame contents scale.
ROTATION/a      Gets the rotation.
ABOUT/a         Gets the rotation point.
CONSTRAIN/s     Gets the proportional scale flag
                state.
PRINT/s         Gets the print flag state.
FILEINFO/a      Gets the file location.
DOCUMENT/s      The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s        The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i      The object number. Default=current.

Results:

The object ID is returned to RESULT.

POSITION stem
left/d             The left coordinate.
top/d              The top coordinate.
right/d            The right coordinate.
bottom/d           The bottom coordinate.
FRAME string/s     The frame state: ON|OFF.
@remark newpanel
CONTENTOFFSET stem
x/d                The horizontal offset.
y/d                The vertical offset.
CONTENTSCALE stem
h/d                The horizontal scale.
v/d                The vertical scale.
ROTATION stem
mode/k             The rotation point: POINT|CENTER.
slant/d            The slant angle.
twist/d            The twist angle.
ABOUT stem
x/d                The point's horizontal coordinate.
y/d                The point's vertical coordinate.
CONSTRAIN string/k The constrain flag: ON|OFF.
PRINT string/k     The print flag: ON|OFF.
FILEINFO stem
mode/k             The file status: INTERNAL|
                   EXTERNAL.
file/s             The filepath and name.

ARexx Examples:

/* will print the eps bounding box */
geteps position coord   
say 'Left:   'coord.left
say 'Top:    'coord.top
say 'Right:  'coord.right
say 'Bottom: 'coord.bottom
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@prev PageStream3:Help/PGS.MD2/getellipse
@endnode

@node GETERRORNUMBER
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETERRORNUMBER                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets the number of the last error. Error numbers are
different from the RC number, which is merely a
measure of the error severity.

@{B}geterrornumber@{UB} @{FG Fill}(no parameters)@{FG Text}

Results:

The number is returned to RESULT.

ARexx Examples:

/* will return the error number and string */
geterrornumber
   errnum=result
geterrorstring
   errname=result
say "Error #"||errnum||" occurred:"
say errname
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETERRORSTRING
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETERRORSTRING                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets a short explanation of the last error. This is
similar to the ARexx errortext() function, except
that this command gets the last PageStream ARexx
error.

@{B}geterrorstring@{UB} @{FG Fill}(no parameters)@{FG Text}

Results:

The message is returned to RESULT.

ARexx Examples:

/* will return the error number and string */
geterrornumber
   errnum=result
geterrorstring
   errname=result
say "Error #"||errnum||" occurred:"
say errname
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETFACINGPAGEDISPLAY
@remark Document Queries

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETFACINGPAGEDISPLAY                                                        @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets the facing page display status.

@{B}getfacingpagedisplay@{UB} [WINDOW name]

WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.

Results:

The facing page display status (ON|OFF) is returned
to RESULT.

ARexx Examples:

getfacingpagedisplay
   if result='ON' then say 'Facing Pages'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETFILE
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETFILE                                                                     @{FG Text}@{UU}

Opens a file selector to get a filename and path from
the user.

@{B}getfile@{UB} <TITLE name> [mode] [PATH name]
[FILE name] [POSBUTTON label] [NEGBUTTON label]

TITLE/s     The file selector title.
mode/k      The file selector type: LOAD (default)|
            SAVE.
PATH/s      The default file path. Default=last.
FILE/s      The default filename to open.
            Default=last.
POSBUTTON/s The label for the positive button.
            Default=Ok.
NEGBUTTON/s The label for the negative button.
            Default=Cancel.

Results:

If NEGBUTTON is chosen, RC is set to 10. If POSBUTTON
is chosen, RC is set to 0 and the full filepath and
name are returned to RESULT.

Notes:

The file selector does not support keyboard
equivalents for buttons, so do not use underscores in
the button labels.

ARexx Examples:

'getfile TITLE "Save a file" save path ram: ¬
   posbutton Save'
   filename=RESULT
   button=RC
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETFILEPATH
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETFILEPATH                                                                 @{FG Text}@{UU}

Opens a file selector to get a file path from the
user.

@{B}getfilepath@{UB} <TITLE name> [PATH path]
[POSBUTTON label] [NEGBUTTON label]

TITLE/s     The file selector title.
PATH/s      The default file path. Default=last.
POSBUTTON/s The label for the positive button.
            Default=Ok.
NEGBUTTON/s The label for the negative button.
            Default=Cancel.

Results:

If NEGBUTTON is chosen, RC is set to 10. If POSBUTTON
is chosen, RC is set to 0 and the path is returned to
result.

Notes:

The file selector does not support keyboard
equivalents for buttons, so do not use underscores in
the button labels.

The ASL path selector is not used because it is a bad
example of interface design. It does not list the
files in the path---not even ghosted---so it is
difficult for the user to know which path to select.
Thus, the file selector is substituted and the
selected file is just ignored.

ARexx Examples:

'getfilepath title "Choose a path" path ram: ¬
   posbutton Choose'
   path=RESULT
   button=RC
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETFONTFAMILIES
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETFONTFAMILIES                                                             @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets the names of all the added font families.

@{B}getfontfamilies@{UB} <stem>

stem/a  Gets the family names.

Results:

The number of font families is returned to RESULT.

stem
0/i     The first family name.
1/i     The second family name.
etc.

ARexx Examples:

getfontfamilies fontnames
   numfonts=result
do count=0 to numfonts-1
   say fontnames.count
end count
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node GETFONTSTYLES
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}GETFONTSTYLES                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Gets the names of all the styles of an added font family.

@{B}getfontstyles@{UB} <family stem>

family/s  The name of the font family.
stem/a    Gets the family's styles.

Results:

The number of styles is returned to RESULT.

stem
0/i       The first style name.
1/i       The second style name.
etc.

ARexx Examples:

getfontstyles Times stylenames
   numstyles=result
do count=0 to numstyles-1
   say stylenames.count
end count
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

